data.name: label34.Text
data.value: To split an area back you should choose the appropriate "Split" button (either for the area or for the minimap). You must split the two minimaps (1:4 and 1:8) separately. After the map is split, folders will be created containing 256x256 chunks which must be copied back to the original folder of the game.

data.name: label33.Text
data.value: Recombining an area results in creation of a JPEG file in "2D Maps" subfolder of ToEE World Builder. Recombining a minimap results in two JPEGs being created, one with 1:4 scaling, and one with 1:8 scaling.

data.name: label32.Text
data.value: To recombine an area map, you should click the "Recombine" button (for complete recombining) or "Recombine Partially" (to recombine a certain M*N block starting at defined X and Y coordinates). You may want to prefer partial recombining if the map is huge (like Map-2-Hommlet-Exterior). If you recombine a huge map completely you may be unable to split it later and get an "Out of memory" error. You have been warned.

data.name: label31.Text
data.value: The areas themselves are stored in "modules/ToEE/art/ground", while the minimaps are located in "modules/ToEE/townmap". You can use corresponding recombiners and splitters to work with either complete areas or with minimaps.

data.name: label29.Text
data.value: The map splitter/recombiner mode can be used to create JPEG images of 2D game maps which can be modified in any image editor (Photoshop, Paint Shop Pro, etc.). Afterwards the combined image can be split back into the form that can be used by the game.

data.name: label212.Text
data.value: If you are editing an original game MOB (e.g. a creature) and experience a strange problem where certain properties (like the Gnolls' DR or Bugbears' AC, or whatever, seems to be "hardcoded" when loading from a MOB file, try pressing the button below that will clean the internal hardcoded information in the .mob file. That will allow you to define more properties from the prototypes (protos)

data.name: label116.Text
data.value:
Sector Visibility Blocking (SVB) related flags are marked with an asterisk (*) symbol. The rule for SVB is: visibility 'extends' (flag 1) out until it hits an 'end' (flag 2). 'Archways' (flag 4) are possibly special kinds of extends that operate in all directions, rather than just up the upper right corner like the way extends do. I'm not really sure what 'base' (flag 3) does.
So if you had a wall that separated a room in the LL (lower left) from a room in the UR (upper right), you'd lay extenders up until the top of the wall, and lay ends at the top. So visibility would uncover up the wall if you're in the room to the LL, but stop at the top of the wall and not uncover even if you were standing in the extenders if you're in the UR room.

data.name: label145.Text
data.value: NOTE: Path nodes control how well the characters can navigate around the map. When there are no path nodes for the map available, the characters can only navigate within a 800x600 screen or so (could be a lot more if they go in straight lines), so they will be unable to move instantly from one end of the map to another (they will need to move in smaller chunks). If you completely redraw the map (make a totally new 2D area with its own blocking) you'll have to delete the pathing data (to avoid weird things with movement). You can try to generate the path nodes using the Path Node Generator utility included with the ToEE World Builder (use the Tools menu).

data.name: label144.Text
data.value: HINT: You can use an area cleaner to delete existing data (objects, clipping parameters, etc.) from the game. You NEED to clean entries marked with (***) if you made a totally new map with absolutely new 2D area graphics!

data.name: label82.Text
data.value: In order to add a long description to the object, choose the corresponding description line from the list, then type something to the "Long Description" field, and click "Update". If you want to remove a long description from the object you should empty the "Long Description" box and click the "Update" button.
